th for a moment, focused and tense, then relaxes as he listens. His expression changes from concentration to clear pleasure; he smiles broadly, almost grinning, while still wearing the headset.\n\nA wider view of the aircraft cabin shows several passengers seated and moving about. The man rises or turns partly in his seat, still wearing the earphones, while a female flight attendant or airline employee in a dark uniform with a red accent stands nearby. Other passengers look on casually. He glances back over the seat behind him, as if sharing or reacting to what he has just heard.\n\nNearby, a young white woman with shoulder-length reddish-brown hair smiles warmly across the aisle or seat row. She wears a patterned blouse with large circular shapes and a tied scarf-like collar. She looks toward an elderly white woman seated beside or in front of her. The elderly woman has neatly styled white hair, black-framed glasses, pearl earrings, and a striped scarf or collar at her neck. She smiles and laughs, then looks downward with an amused expression, suggesting the good mood has spread among the passengers.\n\nThe man is seen again from behind and in profile, still seated with the headset in one ear, looking over his shoulder. White serif text appears over the lower left and center of the cabin image: “The friendly skies of your land.” As the man lowers behind the seatback, the slogan remains prominent across the seat in front of him. The commercial ends on a blue screen with large white serif lettering: “United to 113 cities.”",
